@NODE "History"

 History
 =======
 V45.65 (1.8.2007):   - address update

                      - memory-related optimizations

 V45.56 (13.1.2007):  - optimized bitmap allocation for pic-dt V42+

 V45.55 (26.11.2006): - fixed some minor issues
                      - major rework of .guide file
                      - upgraded datatype engine to latest code
                      - updated installer script
                      - OS versions below OS 3.1 no longer supported
                      - changed name from "faxx" to "akFAXX" to
                        reflect who's maintaining it
                      - now is able to load page 1
                        of multi-page fax files;
                        previously the file recognition
                        did not work at all;
                        CAT chunk support
                      - also supports exotic CAT
                        chunks with starting NULL
                        chunk
                      - FAXX and other decoder tables/structs
                        now "const"
                      - disabled support for
                        compression type 2,
                        since those files obviously
                        are not handled correctly
                        at the moment (not sure why)
                      - more graceful exit on odd errors
                      - memory allocation now using pools
                      - 030/040/060 version accidentally were linked
                        against math libraries (no harm)
                      - added X/Y Aspect calculation
                      - replaced bestmode calculation
                      - no longer clearing dest bitmap

 V43.14 (9.10.98):    - updated installer
                      - updated docs
                      - small changes

 V43.13 (11.6.98):    - spatch tool was missing, causing the installer
                        script to fail. Added tool plus note in the docs.
                        (-> Bernd Rehlinger)

 V43.12 (5.6.98):     - updated akDT_Installer by Robert C. Reiswig
                        (-> Robert C. Reiswig, akDatatype@vgr.com)

 V43.11 (10.4.98) :   - FAXX files without GPHD header would not
                        have been read at all (introduced in 43.10 ?)
                        (-> Jürgen Urbanek)
                      - FAXX files written by MultiFax sometimes seem
                        to be decoded badly. Reason unknown yet (decoder
                        bad or encoder faulty ?)
                        (-> Jürgen Urbanek)
                      - added note on problems with foreign, non-standard FAXX files
                        (and follow-up clearification by Tkr)
                      - 030/040/060 versions now generated from patches
                      - added new, improved Installer script by
                        Robert C. Reiswig (-> a lot of credits
                        hereby go to his address :-)

 V43.10 (11.3.98) :   - fixed descriptor
                      - replaced buggy dispatcher code from 43.7
                      - improved code generation
                      - probably faster
                      - viewmode generation isn't finalized yet
                      - updated docs

 V43.7 (29.9.97) :    - rewrote Dispatch() routine completely,
                        implemented new routines derived
                        from Roland Mainz' improved sample code
                      - DTM_WRITE now can be forced to its
                        old behaviour by specifying the hidden
                        prefs option "OLD_DTM_WRITE"
                        (IFF-ILBM then will be written without
                         any error code given because of
                         unsupported DTWR_RAW)
                      - updated docs

 V43.6 (8.9.97)  :    - updated docs
                      - updated akDT_Installer by Robert C. Reiswig
                      - installer icon was missing
                      - better (compiler) optimization

 V43.5 (12.8.97)  :   - recompiled with SAS/C V6.58
                      - updated URLs (GPSoftware)
                      - added akDT_Installer by Robert C. Reiswig
                        (-> Robert C. Reiswig, akDatatype@vgr.com)

 V43.4 (4.7.97)  :    - fixed "memory loss on LibInit failure" bug, #2

 V43.3 (26.4.97)  :   - fixed "memory loss on LibInit failure" bug
                      - Dispatcher code now gracefully handles
                        DTM_WRITE (rejection) and other source media
                        than supported (rejected, too)

 V43.2 (10.6.97)   :  - public release on Aminet

 V43.1             :  - internal version

